==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English ''chapiter'' < Old French [[chapitre]] < Latin [[capitulum]] ("little head") < [[caput]] ("head") < Proto-Indo-European '''*kauput-''' ("head").

===Noun===
'''chapter''' (''plural:'' [[chapters]])

#One of the main [[section]]s into which the text of a [[book]] is divided.
#An administrative division of an [[organization]], usually [[local]] to a specific [[area]].

